    <description>This is a Record-Triggered Flow.
Upon trigger, the flow first checks if the SMS direction is &apos;Incoming&apos;. If true, it queries the database for an existing SMS record with the same &apos;From_Number__c&apos; but not the current record&apos;s &apos;Id&apos;. If found, it proceeds to check for related records [Lead, Account, or Host] based on the phone number. If any related record is found, it&apos;s assigned to the SMS record. If no related record is found, the flow attempts to find a Lead, Account, or Host using the &apos;From_Number__c&apos; and assigns the record&apos;s &apos;Id&apos; to the SMS record.

Several objects and their fields worth mentioning. Below are the details (the format is given as: object_name - field_name: interaction)
  * SMS__c - Direction__c : The flow uses this field to filter incoming SMS records.
  * SMS__c - To_Number__c : The flow uses this field to search for existing SMS records.
  * SMS__c - Lead__c : The flow assigns the related Lead&apos;s Id to this field.
  * SMS__c - Account__c : The flow assigns the related Account&apos;s Id to this field.
  * SMS__c - Host__c : The flow assigns the related Host&apos;s Id to this field.</description>
